Sentencas: Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1- xVxO3-delta (SYTV) with perovskite structure was investigated as an alternative anode to utilize H2S containing fuels in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Characteristics of Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xVxO3-δ(x = 0.01, 0.04, 0.07, 0.12) Anode for Using H2S Containing Fuel in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: To improve the electrochemical performance of Sr0.92Y0.08TiO3-delta (SYT), vanadium(V) was substituted to titanium(Ti) at the B-site of the SYT perovskites.
Titulo: Characteristics of Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xVxO3-δ(x = 0.01, 0.04, 0.07, 0.12) Anode for Using H2S Containing Fuel in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The SYTV synthesized by the Pechini method was chemically compatible with the YSZ electrolyte without additional by-products formation under the cell fabricating conditions.
Titulo: Characteristics of Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xVxO3-δ(x = 0.01, 0.04, 0.07, 0.12) Anode for Using H2S Containing Fuel in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: As increasing V substitution amounts, the oxygen vacancies increased, resulting to increasing ionic conductivity of the anode.
Titulo: Characteristics of Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xVxO3-δ(x = 0.01, 0.04, 0.07, 0.12) Anode for Using H2S Containing Fuel in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The cell performance in pure H-2 at 850 degrees C is 19.30 mW/cm(2) and 34.87 mW/cm(2) for a 1 mol.% and 7 mol.% of V substituted anodes, respectively.
Titulo: Characteristics of Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xVxO3-δ(x = 0.01, 0.04, 0.07, 0.12) Anode for Using H2S Containing Fuel in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The cell performance using H-2 fuel containing 1000 ppm of H2S at 850 degrees C was 23.37 mW/cm(2) and 73.11 mW/cm(2) for a 1 mol.% and 7 mol.% of V substituted anodes, respectively.
Titulo: Characteristics of Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xVxO3-δ(x = 0.01, 0.04, 0.07, 0.12) Anode for Using H2S Containing Fuel in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
